# Folder Structure (Screaming Architecture)

The folder structure should "scream" the intent of the application. Looking at the `/features` folder should immediately tell you what the application does.

## Root Structure

```
src/
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ app/
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ core/           # Singleton services, guards, interceptors
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ shared/         # Reusable components, pipes, directives
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ features/       # Feature modules (THE MAIN FOLDERS)
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ app.component.ts
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ app.config.ts
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ app.routes.ts
в”‚
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ environments/       # Environment configurations
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ styles/             # Global styles, variables, themes
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ assets/             # Static assets
в””в”Ђв”Ђ index.html
```

## Core Module (`/core`)

Singleton services and app-wide infrastructure:

```
core/
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ services/
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ api.service.ts          # Base HTTP service
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ auth.service.ts         # Authentication
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ storage.service.ts      # LocalStorage/SessionStorage
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ notification.service.ts # Toast/snackbar notifications
в”‚
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ interceptors/
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ auth.interceptor.ts     # Add auth headers
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ error.interceptor.ts    # Global error handling
в”‚
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ guards/
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ auth.guard.ts           # Route protection
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ role.guard.ts           # Role-based access
в”‚
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ models/
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ api.models.ts           # Shared API interfaces
в”‚
в””в”Ђв”Ђ tokens/
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ injection-tokens.ts     # DI tokens
```

**Rules for `/core`:**
- Services are `providedIn: 'root'` (singletons)
- No components in core
- No feature-specific logic
- Only app-wide, cross-cutting concerns

